genresAdvancedInfo.name: adelaide punk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Adelaide punk is a subgenre of punk rock that emerged in Adelaide, Australia in the late 1970s. It is characterized by its fast, aggressive sound, politically charged lyrics, and DIY ethos. Adelaide punk bands often play small, underground venues and are known for their energetic live performances. Some notable Adelaide punk bands include The Exploding White Mice, The Mark of Cain, and The Hard-Ons.
